args:
The party hurries to a town under attack and
discovers Tiki, the Divine Dragon princess.
After witnessing an imperial dragon hunt,
Tiki has deemed the humans of this world to
be her enemy. The prince's party then confronts
her in the hopes of convincing her otherwise.
Attend me, men! Our orders are to root out\nand exterminate every last dragon on this\nmountainâ€”leave not a single one alive!
Huh? What's a kid doin' out here?!
Stop it! Stop hurting the dragons!
No one cares what you think, child.\nNow go home before you get hurt.
If you don't stop, I'm going to get angry!
If you do any more bad things,\nI'm going to make you pay!
Stand your ground, you gutless curs!\nWe're under orders to slay those dragons\nas an offering to the Empress!
Fine! Be that way! Don't blame me\nfor what happens next!
F-fall back! We need to regroup!
Well, that did the trick for now,\nbut I'm pretty sure they'll be back.
This world is just like that woman\ntold me it would be...
...Huh? Wh-where am I?\nAnd where is everyone else?
So the Dragon Scion has awakened.
You have naught to fear from me;\nI've no intentions of harming you.\nI seek only to borrow your might.
No! I'm not going to help a\nbad person like you!
Ah, but you misunderstand. What I desire\nfrom you is nothing less than the salvation\nof an entire world's dragons.

In the world of which I speak, dragons
are a symbol of faith. Nevertheless,
the ascension of a wicked demon has
left them subject to terrible persecution.
But again, I speak of a different world.\nThese endangered dragons are not\nthe manakete that you know.
Yet I would hear your judgment\non the matter. Are such dragons\nworthy of your salvation?
I am a friend to all dragonkind, no matter\nthe origin. If I have the power to aid them,\nthen I will do it!
I expected no less of you, young scion.\nPray allow me to express my admiration\nfor your considerable resolve.

But I also advise you to steel yourself;
the enormity of the threat these dragons
face from the demon-tainted forces may
be rather more than you are expecting.

Hear me, men! Today is the day we wipe
out those foul dragons for good and all!
Now send in the fiends to keep that
golden dragon at bay!
Now's our chance! Slay the other dragons!
Forward, men! Keep the pressure on!
No! They're going to kill them\nand leave me all alone...
...Wait, slow down. You say there's\na dragon attacking the town?!
Could this be some manner\nof misunderstanding?
I wish it was, but every survivor who\nescaped has been spinnin' the same tale.
Do the dragons of this world typically\nattack humans or their settlements?
We have all sorts of dragons in this world,\nand some are much crankier than others.
But going out of the way to attack a\nhuman town is not normal behavior.
Even so, the existence of dragons is\nnot always to humanity's benefit.
For example, as dragons govern nature,\nthey are also responsible for causing\nvarious natural disasters.
Wait, so you blame dragons every time\nthere's a storm or earthquake?!

Er, no. That's not quite right. Such things
are generally caused by disturbances
within the balance of mana as opposed
to the dragon's personal will.
We dragons, you see, possess the power\nto suppress that manaâ€”or, conversely,\nto increase it!

I sure am! This little skinsuit is just
a disguise so I can travel incognito.
In truth, I am the majestic and beautiful
Flamewyrm, Brunhilda!
Fascinating... You know, that actually\nreminds me of a friend of mine who\nis a divine dragon in her own right.
Hey, yeah. Your world's got dragons too,\nright? Something called manaketes?
That's right. And while the manakete\nI refer to comes from a different world,\nwe're still very close friends.
Well, whatever is going on, we can't\nlet this village remain in harm's way.\nLet's go, everyone!
...I don't see any signs of a dragon.\nAre we sure this village ahead\nis the one that's under attack?
Uh, guys? What's a kid doing here?
Tiki! Oh, it's so wonderful to see you!\nEveryone, this my good friend Tiki.\nShe's the divine dragon I told you about.
And I can assure you there's no way she\nis responsible for attacking a village.
You're bad people who do\nawful things to us!
Friend or not, we can't allow this village\nto sustain any more damage.

We're gonna need you to calm down,
my dragon sister. And if that means I
need to start playing rough with you,
then so be it!
Everyone's going away...\nMake this nightmare stop!
